    "recap_headline": "University of Richmond Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BRONX, N.Y. \u2013\nRichmond baseball dropped a 4-3 decision to Fordham in Atlantic 10 Conference action at Houlihan Family Park Sunday afternoon.\nRichmond, now 12-12 on the year and 1-5 in league play, returns to Pitt Field to host Old Dominion for the first of three midweek matchups this season. First pitch is set for 2 p.m. and the game will be streamed on ESPN+.\nFordham got on the board in the first inning off UR starter\nJackson Hinchliffe\non an RBI double down the right field line.\nRichmond answered with a run in the top of the second.\nRJ Rickabaugh\nled off the frame with a walk then scored on\nRyan Recio's\ndouble down the left field line.\nThe Rams took a 2-1 lead in the fourth, connecting two hits and a Spider miscue to score. Hinchliffe went four-plus innings on the mound, scattering two runs on four hits, two walks, a hit batter and one strikeout.\nDylan Winebrenner\nsnagged the lead back for Richmond in the fifth inning on a two-run home run to centerfield, bringing in\nEvan Wilson\nfrom first. Winebrenner now leads the team with eight home runs and 20 RBI.\nDominic Ruggiero took over for Hinchliffe in the fifth and got out of the frame with a double play he started. In the sixth, Ruggiero got two outs, including a strikeout, before he was lifted for\nAaron Van Tuyle\n. Van Tuyle induced a pop-out on the second pitch of his appearance. He went on to toss a scoreless seventh, allowing one hit but collecting the strikeout to end the Rams chances.\nJustin Gay\ntook the mound with one out in the eighth and got two ground outs to strand two Rams. After the Spiders stranded two runners in the top of the ninth, Gay got two flyouts quickly but loaded the bases with a base hit, intentional walk and a hit batter. Fordham got a base hit to right center two score two runs and collect the win.",
